30. How to differentiate static and non-static members?
-->
| Feature    | Static         | Non-static      |
| ---------- | -------------- | --------------- |
| Belongs to | Class          | Object          |
| Memory     | One copy       | Multiple copies |
| Access     | Without object | Needs object    |
| Keyword    | static         | none            |


31. Draw a memory diagram for static members showing where they get memory in the JVM.
-->👉 Static members are stored in Method Area (Class Area)
    👉 Objects are stored in Heap Memory
        JVM MEMORY
   ---------------------
   |   Method Area     |
   |-------------------|
   | static variables  |
   | static methods    |
   | static blocks     |
   ---------------------

   |      Heap         |
   |-------------------|
   | Objects           |
   ---------------------

   |      Stack        |
   |-------------------|
   | Method calls      |
   ---------------------


👉 Key idea:
Static → one copy → Method Area
Non-static → per object → Heap
